==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heathenish
<hw>Hea"then*ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>h⟦aemac⟧⟦edh⟧enisc</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining
to the heathen; resembling or characteristic of heathens.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Worse than <xex>heathenish</xex> crimes.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rude; uncivilized; savage; cruel.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Irreligious; <as>as, a <ex>heathenish</ex> way of
living</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heathenishly</ent>⟦br⟧
